# Anima — environment overrides
#
# Copy to `.env` (it's gitignored) and uncomment what you need:
#
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# Format: KEY=VALUE, one per line, `#` for comments, optional surrounding
# quotes. No shell interpolation. A real process env var always wins over a
# value set here (so `ANIMA_DIT=… make lora` still overrides the file).
#
# `.env` is loaded automatically by anything that calls default_checkpoints()
# — every examples/ script, the bench harness, and the model loaders — so you
# don't have to export these in your shell.

# --- Model paths -------------------------------------------------------------
# Point at weights stored outside the repo's default models/ tree. Relative
# paths resolve under the repo home (ANIMA_HOME); absolute paths pass through.
# Unset → values come from configs/base.toml, then built-in fallbacks.
#ANIMA_DIT=models/diffusion_models/anima-base-v1.0.safetensors
#ANIMA_VAE=models/vae/qwen_image_vae.safetensors
#ANIMA_TEXT_ENCODER=models/text_encoders/qwen_3_06b_base.safetensors

# --- Relocated checkout ------------------------------------------------------
# Absolute path to the anima_lora/ checkout. Set this if you `import anima_lora`
# from another project so repo-relative paths (configs/, models/, output/)
# resolve correctly. Unset → the directory the package lives in.
#ANIMA_HOME=/abs/path/to/anima_lora

# --- Optional: tooling credentials / corpora ---------------------------------
# Hugging Face token for model downloads (or just run `hf auth login`).
#HF=hf_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# ComfyUI registry token for `comfy node publish`.
#COMFY_REG=
# External caption corpus directory (caption-index / tagger tooling).
#CAPTION_CORPUS_DIR=/abs/path/to/captions
